OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPM refuses to say benefits 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwill rise with inflation   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Liz Truss has refused to say benefits  
OL,6, will rise in line with prices, as she  
OL,7, faces questions over how to pay for her
OL,8, government's tax-cutting plans.        
OL,10,FHer predecessor, Boris Johnson, pledged
OL,11,Fbenefits would rise with inflation.    
OL,13,FAsked whether she would maintain this  
OL,14,Fcommitment, Ms Truss told the BBC the  
OL,15,Fgovernment had to be "fiscally         
OL,16,Fresponsible" and bring debt down.      
OL,18,FBut cabinet minister Penny Mordaunt    
OL,19,Fsaid it "makes sense" to increase      
OL,20,Fbenefits in line with inflation.       
